{
    "title": "{A Mother's Grievance}",
    "content": "{It was one of those peculiar days when fate seemed to conspire against me, or perhaps it just so happened that my youngest had stumbled upon a most curious contraption - an 'electric computer', as the modern world calls them. As I approached him in our boudoir with furrowed brow and tightened corset laced uncomfortably across my midriff, he stood frozen before this metal monstrosity that sat coldly on a table between us.}"
