{
"title": "A Mother's Anger",
"content": "{As the sun dipped beneath the horizon, casting long shadows through our home of stone and timber in that fusty old London street we called 'home', a peculiar dissonance grew within my soul. Akin to many mothers before me but uniquely agonizing for I found myself at an impasse not with nappies or nap time conflicts, but rather with those infernal machines they call computers - devices that promised knowledge and convenience yet only delivered bewilderment.}"
    , "word_count":108,"style_elements":[
