    "mother's perspective as the narrator (unreliable)" ]}

{ "title": "The Unspoken Rejection", "content": "At board meetings, Sarah watched as numbers danced before their eyes and decisions were made in whispers. 'We're not funding your department this fiscal year,' her boss said casually, though the tightening of his lips hinted at an unresolved rivalry overshadowing budgets. The company would pivot towards tech upgrades instead. Sarah noted that no one discussed future returns or efficiency gains from these investments—just a passive-aggressive nod to tradition and survival, as some projects were quietly shelved in the name of cutbacks."

